    "comment": "Rationale: knock-out of synaptopodin affects synaptic transmission.\nFig. 4: Reduced hippocampal LTP Field excitatory postsynaptic potentials (fEPSP) measured in the CA1 stratum radiatum were evoked by stimulation of the Schaffer collateral commissural afferents in KO animals.\n\n14/3/2017 Pim\n- The postsynaptic element of the annotation comes from the exclusive localization of SYNPO at the postsynaptic spine apparatus. Interfering with SYNPO expression is therefore inferred to regulate synaptic transmission via a postsynaptic mechanism (also spine apparatus is missing here).. Experimental description: Wild-type (male; n 5) and mutant mice (male; n 5) were deeply anesthetized with an overdose of Nembutal (300 mgkg body weight) (p. 10494)...",
